IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: MSP MARKED VEHICLE MV-30 BODY WORN CAMERA EQUIPPED Attachments: 1. Copy of MSP form 63 Property Record (P-339229). 2. Copy of MSP form 67 Request for laboratory examination/ Chain of Custody Log Scene Processing: A plainview search of the subjects vehicle resulted in the recovery of 51 grams of Cannabis. Physical Evidence: The physical evidence, in this case, is the suspected Cannabis recovered from the front right passenger seat of the defendants vehicle. The total weight of 51 grams as verified by Cpl. Douglas. The CDS was recognized as Cannabis by my training, knowledge, and experience as a Maryland State Trooper. The suspected Cannabis was seized and processed according to MSP policy and regulations. The Cannabis was stored on MSP Form 67 Chain of Custody under the Property Held P-339229. Complaint/Victim: State of Maryland Witness/Neighborhood Check: Due to the nature of the incident, a neighborhood check was not conducted. Suspect: Unknown Narrative: On 06/04/2023, at approximately 0835 hours, I, Trooper Murray #7580 of the Maryland State Police Forestville Barrack, responded to a car accident in the area of 495 Southbound at Allentown Road.. Upon my approach, I noticed a black Honda Accord bearing the MD registration 5BE0266, and a blue Subaru Outback MD registration 1DC4314. During the subsequent investigation, one of the witnesses, Fredy Reyes-Aragon (H/M) informed me that he witnessed one of the drivers drop what he suspected to be cannabis. Aragon showed me where the CDS was located. I seized the suspected cannabis and The suspected cannabis weighed a total 7.5 grams including packaging weight verified by Cpl. Douglas 5631. The above listed CDS was processed in accordance with MSP policy and regulations. All the above events occurred in Prince Georges County, Maryland. I request this case be closed.
